OL,6,FThis would leave the island's 2,100
OL,7,Fresidents dependent on a ferry service
OL,8,F- plus potentially helicopters for
OL,9,Fmedivacs.
OL,11,FMr Roberts says this prospect would be
OL,12,F"catastrophic" from a medical
OL,13,Fperspective, highlighting the
OL,14,Fdependency on air travel of islanders
OL,15,Fwho are accessing treatments in
OL,16,FGuernsey or Southampton.
OL,18,FHe adds: "Boats are being used, but to
OL,19,Fask the sick, elderly, and disabled to
OL,20,Fembark and disembark using a ladder at
OL,21,Fthe Harbour is inadequate.
